main event: Multiple witnesses reported observing a bright object moving through the sky, changing colors and moving in various directions over Green Bay, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The object was observed for over 2 hours and 10 minutes, with multiple witnesses corroborating the sightings.
The object was described as changing colors, white, red, and a flash of green, and was compared to the size of a street light.
A similar object was observed by military personnel in the vicinity, adding credibility to the sightings.
The object appeared to be at a significant distance, with varied descriptions of its location and movement.
No physical evidence or photographs of the object were captured, but the observations were made through ground-visual means.
sighted object: bright object changing colors and moving in various directions
witnesses: multiple witnesses including a supervisor of the observation post and military personnel
